cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on hand pose estimation using depth sensors, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as hand pose estimation is important for robotic manipulation tasks. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category as hand pose estimation is important for creating realistic hand animations in computer graphics. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as hand pose estimation is important for natural and intuitive interaction with AR/VR and wearable devices. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also possible as hand pose estimation is important for gesture recognition in multimedia applications.
